ter","200 g dried Chinese egg noodles","4 spring onions\/shallots, white part only, cut into halves, green part reserved for garnishing","6 garlic cloves","150 g carrots, cut into pieces","1 - 2 fresh chillies, deseeded if preferred","60 g unsalted butter","200 g cabbage, shredded","1 tbsp kecap manis","1 tbsp oyster sauce","1 tbsp soy sauce","¼ tsp ground white pepper","40 g water","15 - 20 snow peas, cut into thin slices","1 - 2 tbsp fried shallots, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r238984","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-hc-xBxDIz1A\/XZQH103mGWI\/AAAAAAAAcMw\/JDJy3jCRdEMQ5dOe6rZIF6U0H_DDdbaHgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_sBlaFesNAq01BSBp.png","title":"Asian-style pork noodles","publishedAt":"2018-07-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25.2 g","fat":"24.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"51.9 g","calories":"2306.9 kJ \/ 549.3 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, frying pan, large bowl, non-stick frying pan, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["Substitute noodles for vegetable zoodles or noodles of choice.","You can serve this dish warm or cold (making it great for lunches the next day)."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","1h","6 portions"]}